    <!-- IMPLEMENT -->
    <div class="case-section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Implement</div>
      <h2>Building a course faculty <em>actually want to teach</em></h2>
      <p>One thing I&rsquo;ve learned from working closely with faculty over the years is that the barrier to using new materials is rarely skepticism about quality. It&rsquo;s time. An adjunct professor teaching three sections of Intro Psych doesn&rsquo;t have hours to read through a guide, build their own slides, and design class activities from scratch. So I built a faculty resource suite that does as much of that work as possible, without removing their voice from the classroom.</p>
      <p>Every module in this course comes with a full Instructor Guide, which includes learning outcomes, a module summary, and detailed write-ups for every classroom activity, each one grounded in evidence-based teaching practices. The guides aren&rsquo;t just activity instructions &mdash; they explain the pedagogical rationale so faculty understand why an activity works, not just how to run it. Alongside the guides, every module also has a complete set of PowerPoint slides ready to use or customize.</p>

