      <div class="reflection">
        <h3>Design Reflection</h3>
        <p>This course has been with me through multiple cyles, multiple platforms, and years of iteration. What I&rsquo;m proudest of isn&rsquo;t any single feature or update cycle &mdash; it&rsquo;s that the course keeps getting more useful. Faculty trust it. Students engage with it. The activities get requested by name. And the work of improving it genuinely excites me, because I can see the impact it has on people who are trying to learn psychology for the first time.</p>
        <p>It also represents the kind of instructional designer I want to be: someone who thinks carefully about learners, builds things that actually work in real classrooms, collaborates well with the people she&rsquo;s working with, and doesn&rsquo;t consider a course &ldquo;done&rdquo; just because it launched.</p>
